================================================================================
Bundled TextMate grammars (syntax highlighting)
================================================================================

The grammar files under src/main/resources/com/editora/grammars/
(*.tmLanguage.json) provide syntax highlighting and come from two sources.

Most grammars were obtained from the shiki "tm-grammars" collection:

    https://github.com/shikijs/textmate-grammars-themes
    (packages/tm-grammars/grammars)

These are aggregated by shiki from their respective upstream projects, each
under its original license (predominantly MIT, with some under other permissive
licenses such as Apache-2.0 or BSD); see the upstream repository above for the
per-grammar license and source attribution. This source includes the Lua,
Dockerfile, Terraform (HCL), TOML, systemd, desktop-entry, and dotenv grammars
(lua/dockerfile/terraform/toml/systemd/desktop/dotenv .tmLanguage.json; systemd,
desktop, and dotenv are under the MIT License). It also includes the SSH config
grammar (ssh-config.tmLanguage.json), which shiki aggregates from
textmate/ssh-config.tmbundle, distributed under that project's permissive
license ("Permission to copy, use, modify, sell and distribute this software is
granted ... provided 'as is' without warranty").

The following grammars were instead obtained from the Eclipse tm4e
"language_pack" (which curates grammars for the tm4e engine used here):

    https://github.com/eclipse-tm4e/tm4e
    (org.eclipse.tm4e.language_pack/syntaxes)

    XML, shell, C, C++, Rust, Ruby, Markdown.

The TypeScript and TypeScriptReact grammars (typescript.tmLanguage.json,
typescriptreact.tmLanguage.json — also used for JavaScript/JSX) were obtained
from Microsoft Visual Studio Code under the MIT License:

    https://github.com/microsoft/vscode
    (extensions/typescript-basics/syntaxes)

    License: MIT  (© Microsoft Corporation)

The PHP grammar (php.tmLanguage.json) was obtained from Microsoft Visual Studio
Code under the MIT License (converted there from KapitanOczywisty/language-php):

    https://github.com/microsoft/vscode
    (extensions/php/syntaxes/php.tmLanguage.json)

    License: MIT  (© Microsoft Corporation; © GitHub Inc. / language-php)

The Caddyfile grammar (caddyfile.tmLanguage.json) was obtained from the official
Caddy VS Code extension under the MIT License:

    https://github.com/caddyserver/vscode-caddyfile
    (syntaxes/caddyfile.tmLanguage.json)

    License: MIT  (© 2023 Matthew Penner)

The crontab and Git config grammars (crontab.tmLanguage.json,
git-config.tmLanguage.json) were obtained from the TextMate bundles
textmate/cron.tmbundle and textmate/git.tmbundle (converted here from the
original plist .tmLanguage to JSON, otherwise unmodified). These bundles are
distributed under TextMate's permissive license: "Permission to copy, use,
modify, sell and distribute this software is granted ... provided 'as is'
without warranty."

    https://github.com/textmate/cron.tmbundle
    https://github.com/textmate/git.tmbundle

The fstab, hosts, and Debian/Ubuntu grammars (fstab.tmLanguage.json,
hosts.tmLanguage.json, deb822.tmLanguage.json, apt-sources.tmLanguage.json,
interfaces.tmLanguage.json, debian-changelog.tmLanguage.json) — like the HTTP
grammar (http.tmLanguage.json) — were written for Editora and are covered by
Editora's own MIT License (above). The .properties files reuse the INI grammar.

These remain under their original upstream licenses (predominantly MIT). All
grammars are redistributed unmodified except markdown.tmLanguage.json (three
regular expressions minimally adjusted for the Joni regex backend — the {,3}
quantifier rewritten as {0,3}, and a variable-length look-behind removed from
the strikethrough rule) and the two plist-to-JSON conversions noted above.

Languages bundled: Java, XML, shell, PowerShell, DOS batch, Python, Groovy,
Kotlin, Ruby, C, C++, Rust, Go, C#, Markdown, JSON, CSS, HTML, YAML, INI, SQL,
systemd, desktop entries, dotenv, SSH config, Git config, crontab, Caddyfile,
fstab, hosts, .properties, deb822 (Debian control / APT sources), APT
sources.list, network interfaces, Debian changelog.

